HEADWORD: Despiteous
<hw>Des*pit"e*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>despitous</ets>, OF. <ets>despiteus</ets>, fr. <ets>despit</ets>;
affected in form by E. <ets>piteous</ets>. See <er>Despite</er>.]</ety>
<def>Feeling or showing despite; malicious; angry to excess; cruel;
contemptuous.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Despiteous</xex>
reproaches.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
